sequenceDiagram
    participant U as 👤 User / Admin
    participant M as Swarm Manager<br/>(Raft Consensus)
    participant C1 as db1 Container<br/>(Patroni Primary)
    participant C2 as db2 Container<br/>(Patroni Replica)
    participant CON as Consul Cluster<br/>(consul1,2,3)
    participant NG as Nginx Stream<br/>(:5000)

    Note over U,NG: Initial State — Cluster Healthy

    M->>M: Reconciliation loop<br/>Desired: db1=1, db2=1
    M->>C1: Health check ✅
    M->>C2: Health check ✅
    M->>M: actual == desired → no action

    Note over C1: 💀 docker kill db1<br/>(simulating crash)

    U->>C1: docker kill db1
    C1-->>C1: Container stops immediately

    M->>M: Task db1 is DEAD<br/>actual (0) < desired (1) → DRIFT!

    rect rgb(255, 200, 200)
        Note over M: ⚡ Reconciliation triggers
        M->>M: Schedule new db1 task
        M->>C1: Create new db1 container<br/>(new container ID, fresh start)
        C1->>C1: entrypoint.sh runs
        C1->>C1: Patroni starts
        C1->>CON: Check leader key
        CON-->>C1: leader = db2
        C1->>C1: Start PostgreSQL as REPLICA
        C1->>C2: Begin streaming replication
        M->>C1: Health check ✅
    end

    Note over C1: db1 recovered as replica<br/>⏱️ ~10-15 seconds

    rect rgb(200, 255, 200)
        Note over CON: Meanwhile — Patroni failover was already handled
        Note over C2: db2 was promoted to primary<br/>during the ~4s Consul TTL window
        NG->>C2: Routes DB traffic to new primary
        Note over NG: App never experienced downtime
    end

    Note over U,NG: ✅ Cluster Self-Healed<br/>1 primary (db2) + 1 replica (db1)<br/>No human intervention needed

    Note over U,NG: Compare: Phase 1 required<br/>manual vagrant up db1<br/>+ wait for VM boot (~30s)
